Programs written in a procedural language are written using a&nbsp;<b>series of step-by-step instructions</b>&nbsp;on how to solve the problem.<br><ul><li>Usually broken down into a number of&nbsp;<b>smaller modules</b>.</li><li>The program consists of a&nbsp;<b>series of calls</b>&nbsp;to procedures or functions.</li><li>Each may in turn call other procedures of functions.</li></ul>